<p>I'm trying to create a form that uploads multiple files from one input rather than multiple and having issues with $_FILES being empty. If I add [] to my input name, the $_FILES is empty. If I take it away, I only get the last submitted file.</p>  <p>HTML code:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;form method="POST" id="upload" enctype="multipart/form-data"&gt;     &lt;p&gt;Choose Files to Upload: &lt;input type="file" name="files[]" form="upload" multiple&gt;&lt;/p&gt; </code></pre>  <p><p></p>         </p>  <p>PHP code:</p>  <pre><code>    if(isset($_POST['submit'])) {       print_r($_FILES);       var_dump($_FILES);     }      function attach_files($id, $resource_type = 'Private::Activity::Task') {      global $workbooks;        $retval = '';      $create_uploads = [];      foreach ($_FILES as &amp;$file) {       $workbooks-&gt;log("Attempting to upload file to task with id $id", $file);     if ($file['error'] == 0) {       $create_uploads = [         'resource_id'   =&gt; $id,         'resource_type' =&gt; $resource_type,         'resource_attribute' =&gt; 'upload_files',         'upload_file[data]' =&gt; [           'tmp_name' =&gt; '@' . $file['tmp_name'],           'file_name' =&gt; $file['name'],           'file_content_type' =&gt; $file['type'],         ],       ];     }     else {       $workbooks-&gt;log('File upload error', $file);       $retval = ' Some files were not uploaded successfully.';     }   }    if (!empty($create_uploads)) {     // Always use the ('content_type' =&gt; multipart/form-data) option for uploading files: it is efficient.     $response = $workbooks-&gt;create('resource_upload_files', $create_uploads, [], ['content_type' =&gt; 'multipart/form-data']);     if ($workbooks-&gt;condensedStatus($response) != 'ok') { return ' Failed to upload files.'; }   }   return $retval; } // attach_files() </code></pre>  <p>I've tried a couple of things:</p>  <p>Changing <code>"multiple"</code> to <code>multiple="multiple"</code> in my HTML Changing the name to an array e.g. <code>name="files[]"</code> instead of <code>name="files"</code></p>  <p>I've found lots of posts with similar errors but nothing specific to what I am experiencing. Any ideas?</p>